以下係用你提供嘅詞語造嘅廣東話句子：

3. 養聲
廣東話：歌手開騷前一定要好好養聲，唔好食冰同講太多嘢。
English: Singers must take good care of their vocal cords before a concert and avoid eating ice or talking too much.

4. 票尾
廣東話：我將張戲票嘅票尾搣低留低，萬一有問題可以用作收據。
English: I tore off the stub of the ticket and kept it just in case I need it as a receipt for any issues.

5. hacker
廣東話：個 hacker 入侵咗公司嘅系統，偷走咗好多客戶資料。
English: The hacker hacked into the company's system and stole a lot of customer data.

6. 石斛蘭
廣東話：屋企陽台種咗幾盆石斛蘭，佢哋好耐先開花，但係好靚。
English: I planted a few pots of Dendrobium on the balcony; they take a long time to bloom, but they are beautiful.

7. 吊詭 (矛盾、悖論)
廣東話：呢個邏輯問題真係好吊詭，點樣都解唔到。
English: This logical problem is really paradoxical; no matter how I try, I can't solve it.

8. 吊詭 (似非而是、荒謬)
廣東話：世事真係好吊詭，越急越做唔到，慢慢嚟反而快。
English: Life is really ironic; the more you rush, the less you get done, but taking it slow actually works faster.

9. 各為其主
廣東話：兩隊球員雖然私交好好，但係上咗場就各為其主，拼到好勁。
English: Although the players from the two teams are good friends off the field, once they are on it, they play for their respective teams and compete fiercely.

10. 軨蓋
廣東話：我部車嘅軨蓋壞咗，要送去車房換新嘅。
English: The rim cover of my car is broken, and I need to take it to the garage to get a new one.

11. 打哥夫
廣東話：佢週末經常同班老友去打哥夫，放鬆心情。
English: He often goes to play golf with his old friends on weekends to relax.

12. 免揀
廣東話：呢間店賣嘅衣服係免揀嘅，買咗就唔可以退。
English: The clothes sold in this shop are non-selectable; once you buy them, you cannot return them.

13. 擺闊佬
廣東話：佢成日去高檔餐廳擺闊佬，其實根本冇咁多錢。
English: He always goes to high-end restaurants to show off his wealth, but he actually doesn't have that much money.

14. 廣播劇
廣東話：我每日返工路上都會聽緊一套懸疑嘅廣播劇。
English: I listen to a suspenseful radio drama every day on my way to work.

15. 錄影機
廣東話：屋企裝咗部錄影機，可以隨時睇返屋企嘅情況。
English: We installed a video recorder at home so we can check what's happening at home anytime.

16. 吟詩吟唔甩
廣東話：證據擺喺度，佢想抵賴都係吟詩吟唔甩。
English: The evidence is right there; no matter how hard he tries, he can't deny it.

17. 佈道大會
廣東話：教會每個禮拜日都會舉行佈道大會，吸引好多新人參加。
English: The church holds a preaching conference every Sunday, attracting many new attendees.

18. 寫手 (寫作的人)
廣東話：佢係一名自由寫手，專門為雜誌撰寫專欄文章。
English: He is a freelance writer who specializes in writing column articles for magazines.

19. 寫手 (代替他人寫作的人)
廣東話：因為佢太忙，所以請咗個寫手幫佢寫畢業論文。
English: Because he was too busy, he hired a ghostwriter to help him write his graduation thesis.

20. 代打
廣東話：佢最近好忙，所以請朋友幫佢代打遊戲。
English: He has been very busy lately, so he asked a friend to play games for him.

21. 茶碗
廣東話：佢收藏咗好多日本傳統嘅茶碗，每一隻都好精緻。
English: He collects many traditional Japanese tea bowls, and each one is very exquisite.

22. 茶隔
廣東話：用茶隔可以將茶葉同茶湯分開，飲起上嚟更順滑。
English: Using a tea strainer separates the tea leaves from the tea liquor, making it smoother to drink.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈
廣東話：公司規矩只許主管遲到，唔許員工遲到，真係只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈。
English: The company rules only allow managers to be late, but not employees; it's truly "only the magistrate is allowed to set fires, but the commoners are not allowed to light lamps."

24. 獨唱
廣東話：演唱會最後一首歌係佢獨唱，感動晒全場觀眾。
English: The last song of the concert was sung by him alone, moving the entire audience.

25. 快人快事
廣東話：佢做事快人快事，從來唔會拖泥帶水。
English: He gets things done quickly and efficiently, never dragging his feet.

26. 四腳獸
廣東話：我哋去公廁嘅時候要小心啲，唔好俾人話係四腳獸。
English: We should be careful when we go to the restroom so we don't get called "four-legged beasts."

27. 無米粥
廣東話：我哋而家只係煲緊無米粥，等條件成熟先正式簽約。
English: We are just having preliminary talks for now; we'll sign the formal contract once the conditions are ripe.

28. 義會
廣東話：以前鄉下人會組織義會，大家集資幫補急用。
English: In the past, people in rural areas would organize mutual aid associations to pool funds for emergencies.

29. 榜文
廣東話：古代皇帝會貼出榜文，宣佈重要嘅政令。
English: In ancient times, emperors would post official notices to announce important decrees.

30. MK名
廣東話：佢個社交媒體帳號用咗一個 MK名，充滿咗奇怪嘅符號。
English: His social media account uses an MK name, filled with strange symbols. [end of text]


